      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Your thoughts describe dissociation and burnout, where the world feels hollow because your routine lacks genuine connection or purpose. This feeling is a cry for meaning, not a desire for actual absence, though the pain is very real right now. Please consider reaching out to a mental health professional who can listen without judgment and help you find anchors in your life. You matter enough that external worlds changing would be a form of loss, not relief.",
      "source": "target",
